Section 3: 

This law applies to the processing of digital personal data (such as your name, phone number, or photo stored on the internet or a computer) within India. It comes into effect whether your data is already in digital form or is initially written on paper and subsequently digitised. Interestingly, even if a foreign company operating outside India processes the digital data of Indians to offer them goods or services, this law will still apply to them.
​Examples and Exceptions (Where it will not apply):
This law does not apply to your personal or domestic matters. Furthermore, if you have voluntarily made any of your data publicly available on the internet, these rules will not apply to that data.
​Example: Suppose a girl named Anjali writes a blog on social media and willingly posts her email and city name there. Since Anjali has made this information public on her own, the provisions of this law will not apply to that data.
